            <title>[JDK-8298081] DiagnoseSyncOnValueBasedClasses doesn&apos;t report useful information for virtual threads</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8298081</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The mechanism used by DiagnoseSyncOnValueBasedClasses to show where the sync occurs only reports platform/carrier thread stack details. That is no use if the code is being executed by a virtual thread. We can use the code being introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8292674&quot; title=&quot;ReportJNIFatalError should print all java frames&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8292674&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8292674&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for JNI error/warning reporting to show the virtual thread stack instead.</description>
